            </p>
            <h3>Post-Study Work Visa (D-2-7)</h3>
            <ul class="checkmark-list">
              <li>International students who have completed their degree programs in South Korea are eligible to apply for a post-study work visa known as the D-2-7 visa.</li>
              <li>The D-2-7 visa allows graduates to stay in South Korea and seek employment opportunities related to their field of study for up to six months.</li>
              <li>During this period, graduates can explore job opportunities, attend interviews, and secure employment in South Korea.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3><strong>Part-Time Job Opportunities:</strong></p></h3>

            <p>Some of the part-time jobs available to international students in South Korea include:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>
                <strong>Retail Assistant:</strong> Working in retail stores, supermarkets, or convenience stores involves tasks like cashiering, stocking shelves, and assisting customers. It's a common part-time job
                that offers flexible hours and an opportunity to improve communication skills.
              </li>
              <li><strong>Hospitality Staff: </strong>Jobs in the hospitality sector include working in restaurants, cafes, or hotels. Duties may involve serving customers, food preparation, or housekeeping.</li>
              <li>
               <strong> Tutor or Teaching Assistant:</strong> Nepalese students proficient in certain subjects or languages can work as tutors or teaching assistants. This job involves helping other students with
                their studies, providing guidance, and facilitating learning. It's a rewarding opportunity to share knowledge and support peers.
              </li>
              <li>
               <strong> Administrative Support:</strong> Working in offices or administrative settings includes tasks like data entry, filing, and providing general office support. It's a role that enhances
                organizational and time management skills while offering exposure to office operations.
              </li>
              <li>
              <strong>  Delivery Services:</strong> Some students may find part-time work in restaurant delivery services or courier companies. This job involves delivering orders or packages to customers' locations.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Event Staffing:</strong> Students can serve as event staff for conferences, concerts, or other events. Responsibilities may include ticketing, ushering, or event setup. It's an exciting job
